The paper deals with the enhancement and detection of 3D vessel-like structures in biomedical images, which is a common problem in computer vision and medical imaging. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses mathematical morphology, which is a subfield of image processing and analysis, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely category. The proposed method involves the use of structuring elements, which is a common technique in signal processing and information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category. The paper also validates the proposed method on synthetic and real data, which involves numerical simulations and data analysis, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with the enhancement of 3D structures, which involves geometric modeling and visualization, making cs.GR (Graphics) a possible category.
